               <msContents>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 21; Nelson collection no. N276.  Paches, son of Parates is Muhs' Taxpayer 28.  1/6 (silver) kite or 2 obols is the price of 1 kotule or 0.27 liter of oil.  The scribe Esminis was responsible for many other price of oil receipts from Thebes between years 30 and 38 of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)</note>
